# Setup FileZilla


### File Transfer Protocol - FTP
* How files are sent over the internet

### Install FileZilla Software
* [Download FileZilla Client](https://filezilla-project.org/download.php?type=client)
* Do not enable any extra features


### Server URL
Find the email from Bluehost that looks like...

![](img/bluehost_info.png)


### Identify the Domain
* This could be the Domain that you registered
* Or one assigned to you by Bluehost


### Site Manager
* File, Site Manager
* New Site (Bluehost)


### Setup FileZilla login
* General Tab - Configure login
    * Host: Bluehost domain
    * Logon Type: Normal
    * User: Bluehost user
    * Password: Bluehost password

![](img/filezilla3.png)


### Setup FileZilla Directories
* Advanced Tab - Configure directories
    * Default Local Directory (browse to "bacs200")
    * Default Remote Directory "/public_html/bacs200"

![](img/filezilla2.png)


### Using FileZilla
* Transfer files

![](img/filezilla.png)


### Uploading files
* Always match up the local and remote panes

